title: SFH on drug issues and vaccination
content_text:
p>
Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Secretary for Food and 
Health, Dr York Chow, at a stand-up media session at the Legislative Council 
Building today (March 31): Reporter: You mention that the Review Committee is going to hold meeting on 
Friday. Can you give details? Are you just holding a meeting or are they 
going to start an investigation on Friday? Secretary for Food and Health: I think we have to address some of the issues 
that we have raised, we have actually outlined them in the panel paper

that we have raised, we have actually outlined them in the panel paper 
today. There are all 12 areas that we need to discuss. Of course, in one 
meeting, we cannot discuss everything. Perhaps, we should prioritise those 
areas and are able to form smaller working groups in order to follow up on 
those issues. I believe that with the broad representation from various 
stakeholders and also the participation from relevant government departments 
as well as the Hospital Authority, we are able to come up with very fruitful

as well as the Hospital Authority, we are able to come up with very fruitful 
recommendations in a short time. Reporter: (The vaccine) Secretary for Food and Health: I think the Department of Health has 
discussed with various stakeholders including the private doctors prior to 
these current recommendations. Of course, we would like to see what new 
ideas the private sectors have right now, whether we can actually have their 
participation in future. But as I have explained earlier, at the moment, the 
infant vaccination programme (Hong Kong Childhood Immunisation Programme)

infant vaccination programme (Hong Kong Childhood Immunisation Programme) has been very effective through our Maternal and Child Health Centres. So I think this is the right way to do, to start with. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript.)
